## Terminology preferences

Use these consistently across all emitted artifacts (YAML, verbalization, PyRel). Locked at project init.

| Concept | Preferred term | Avoid |
|---|---|---|
| Entity instance | "instance" | "row", "record", "tuple" |
| Fact-type instance | "fact" | "row" (when discussing a fact-type extension) |
| Uniqueness constraint | "uniqueness" or "UC" | "key constraint" |
| Mandatory role | "mandatory" | "required", "not null" (in conceptual discussion) |
| Subtype | "subtype" | "subclass", "subentity" |

The skill's reference files use these terms. If you override here, you accept that downstream verbalizations may read differently from the skill's examples.

